# Personal Website Project Lifecycle Rule

## Rule Name: erenkeskinoglu-website-lifecycle
Description: A comprehensive guide for developing a personal website with interactive tools like Killer Sudoku Helper and Crypto Analyzer. This lifecycle is specifically tailored for Eren Keskinoglu's personal website project.

## 1. Planning & Analysis Phase
### Requirements Gathering
- [ ] Define site content sections (Home, About, Projects, Interactive Tools, Media Corner, Contact)
- [ ] Detail requirements for interactive tools (Killer Sudoku Helper, Crypto Analyzer)
- [ ] Plan how to showcase projects, books, movies, and games
- [ ] Map out technology stack (Next.js, Tailwind CSS, React Hook Form, etc.)
- [ ] Define site personality and voice
- [ ] Plan mobile experience

### Documentation
- [ ] Create site map with all sections and pages
- [ ] Document user flows (especially for interactive tools)
- [ ] Define SEO strategy
- [ ] Create content calendar

## 2. Design Phase
### Architecture Design
- [ ] Design data structures for projects and media collections
- [ ] Plan API endpoints for interactive tools
- [ ] Create component hierarchy
- [ ] Define state management approach

### Detailed Design
- [ ] Design main site layout and navigation
- [ ] Create UI designs for all main sections
- [ ] Design interactive tools interfaces
- [ ] Create design system (colors, typography, spacing, components)
- [ ] Design dark/light mode themes

## 3. Development Phase
### Setup
- [ ] Configure Next.js with TypeScript
- [ ] Set up Tailwind CSS
- [ ] Configure project aliases and folder structure
- [ ] Set up linting and formatting

### Implementation
- [ ] Develop core layout and navigation components
- [ ] Implement main sections (Home, About, Projects)
- [ ] Create dedicated "Tools" section
- [ ] Implement Killer Sudoku Helper
- [ ] Implement Crypto Analyzer tool
- [ ] Develop media showcase section (books, movies, games)
- [ ] Implement contact form
- [ ] Add animations and transitions
- [ ] Implement SEO optimization

## 4. Testing Phase
### Test Planning
- [ ] Create test cases for each interactive tool
- [ ] Define responsive design test scenarios
- [ ] Plan performance testing

### Test Execution
- [ ] Test all sections on mobile, tablet, desktop
- [ ] Verify interactive tools functionality
- [ ] Test dark/light mode switching
- [ ] Test form submission
- [ ] Verify SEO elements
- [ ] Run performance tests (Lighthouse)
- [ ] Check accessibility compliance

## 5. Deployment Phase
### Preparation
- [ ] Set up domain (erenkeskinoglu.com)
- [ ] Configure hosting on Vercel
- [ ] Set up analytics

### Deployment
- [ ] Deploy to staging environment
- [ ] Conduct final tests on staging
- [ ] Deploy to production
- [ ] Verify live site functionality
- [ ] Submit sitemap to search engines

## 6. Maintenance & Enhancement
### Ongoing Maintenance
- [ ] Regular content updates
- [ ] Add new projects
- [ ] Enhance existing interactive tools
- [ ] Add new tools over time
- [ ] Update media recommendations

### Feedback & Iteration
- [ ] Collect visitor feedback
- [ ] Monitor tool usage
- [ ] Implement improvements based on feedback
- [ ] Iterate on design and functionality

## Important Guidelines
- Ensure tools are practically useful, not just demonstrations
- Maintain a cohesive design language throughout
- Optimize images and assets for performance
- Ensure interactive tools work well on mobile
- Keep content fresh and up-to-date
- Balance professional showcase with personal interests

